"{\"uid\": \"lewrockwell.com-2024-08-no_author-america-2-0-goes-to-the-satanic-olympics\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"August 5, 2024 I used to enjoy watching the Olympics.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 54, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 40, \"to\": 52}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When I was still young and naive, I actually rooted for Americans in all events.\", \"from\": 55, \"to\": 135, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Americans\", \"from\": 111, \"to\": 120}, {\"ngram\": \"all events\", \"from\": 124, \"to\": 134}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I loved the diving in particular, and the female gymnastics was fun to watch as well.\", \"from\": 136, \"to\": 221, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the diving\", \"from\": 144, \"to\": 154}, {\"ngram\": \"the female gymnastics\", \"from\": 174, \"to\": 195}]}, {\"sentence\": \"America took the moral high ground, and only allowed amateurs to compete for them.\", \"from\": 222, \"to\": 304, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"America\", \"from\": 222, \"to\": 229}, {\"ngram\": \"the moral high ground\", \"from\": 235, \"to\": 256}, {\"ngram\": \"amateurs\", \"from\": 275, \"to\": 283}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unlike the dirty, rotten commie Soviets.\", \"from\": 305, \"to\": 345, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the dirty, rotten commie Soviets\", \"from\": 312, \"to\": 344}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They stripped the medals won by Jim Thorpe in the 1912 Olympics from him, when it was discovered that he'd played semi-professional baseball beforehand.\", \"from\": 347, \"to\": 499, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 379, \"end\": 389, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jim_Thorpe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.413438724426659e-22, \"text\": \"Jim Thorpe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jim_Thorpe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jim_Thorpe\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the medals\", \"from\": 361, \"to\": 371}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1912 Olympics\", \"from\": 393, \"to\": 410}, {\"ngram\": \"semi-professional baseball\", \"from\": 461, \"to\": 487}]}, {\"sentence\": \"American leaders got a lot of mileage out of that one; the man who was for a long time considered the greatest athlete who ever lived, lost his medals because we were better than the communists, who trained and sent professional athletes to compete.\", \"from\": 500, \"to\": 749, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 500, \"end\": 508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999999881896663, \"rank\": 1.1712885678060396e-07, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 521, \"to\": 526}, {\"ngram\": \"mileage\", \"from\": 530, \"to\": 537}, {\"ngram\": \"the man\", \"from\": 555, \"to\": 562}, {\"ngram\": \"a long time\", \"from\": 575, \"to\": 586}, {\"ngram\": \"the greatest athlete\", \"from\": 598, \"to\": 618}, {\"ngram\": \"his medals\", \"from\": 640, \"to\": 650}, {\"ngram\": \"the communists\", \"from\": 679, \"to\": 693}, {\"ngram\": \"professional athletes\", \"from\": 716, \"to\": 737}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Against our wide-eyed, innocent amateurs.\", \"from\": 750, \"to\": 791, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our wide-eyed, innocent amateurs\", \"from\": 758, \"to\": 790}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When USA only won the bronze medal in basketball at the 1988 Olympics, suddenly all that moral fervor was forgotten.\", \"from\": 792, \"to\": 908, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"USA\", \"from\": 797, \"to\": 800}, {\"ngram\": \"the bronze medal\", \"from\": 810, \"to\": 826}, {\"ngram\": \"basketball\", \"from\": 830, \"to\": 840}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1988 Olympics\", \"from\": 844, \"to\": 861}, {\"ngram\": \"all that moral fervor\", \"from\": 872, \"to\": 893}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And so we formed the \\\"Dream Team\\\" of NBA greats, so they would easily win the gold in men's basketball.\", \"from\": 909, \"to\": 1012, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 931, \"end\": 941, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9996406952145133, \"rank\": 0.0003594339316104905, \"text\": \"Dream Team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 946, \"end\": 949, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.776135488817447e-14, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the gold\", \"from\": 983, \"to\": 991}, {\"ngram\": \"men's basketball\", \"from\": 995, \"to\": 1011}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And they did, proudly hoisting the same medals that poor Jim Thorpe had stolen from him.\", \"from\": 1013, \"to\": 1101, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the same medals\", \"from\": 1044, \"to\": 1059}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the record, Jim Thorpe never made millions of dollars dunking a ball.\", \"from\": 1102, \"to\": 1175, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1118, \"end\": 1128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jim_Thorpe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.413438724426659e-22, \"text\": \"Jim Thorpe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jim_Thorpe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jim_Thorpe\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the record\", \"from\": 1106, \"to\": 1116}, {\"ngram\": \"millions\", \"from\": 1140, \"to\": 1148}, {\"ngram\": \"dollars\", \"from\": 1152, \"to\": 1159}, {\"ngram\": \"a ball\", \"from\": 1168, \"to\": 1174}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thorpe, in fact, ravaged by alcoholism, died in poverty.American Memory Hole: ...Jeffries, DonaldCheck Amazon for Pricing.\", \"from\": 1176, \"to\": 1298, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1176, \"end\": 1182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremy_Thorpe\", \"score\": 0.9999992035458024, \"rank\": 7.878325637312073e-07, \"text\": \"Thorpe\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremy_Thorpe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jeremy_Thorpe\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fact\", \"from\": 1187, \"to\": 1191}, {\"ngram\": \"alcoholism\", \"from\": 1204, \"to\": 1214}, {\"ngram\": \"poverty\", \"from\": 1224, \"to\": 1231}, {\"ngram\": \"American Memory Hole\", \"from\": 1232, \"to\": 1252}, {\"ngram\": \"Jeffries\", \"from\": 1257, \"to\": 1265}, {\"ngram\": \"DonaldCheck Amazon\", \"from\": 1267, \"to\": 1285}, {\"ngram\": \"Pricing\", \"from\": 1290, \"to\": 1297}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So I started rooting against America in pretty much every competition after that.\", \"from\": 1300, \"to\": 1381, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"America\", \"from\": 1329, \"to\": 1336}, {\"ngram\": \"every competition\", \"from\": 1352, \"to\": 1369}]}, {\"sentence\": \"How could you not root for a Serbia or Croatia against a team of entitled and pampered multi-millionaires?\", \"from\": 1382, \"to\": 1488, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1411, \"end\": 1417, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"score\": 0.9999997203731645, \"rank\": 2.4709371781658265e-07, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\"}, {\"begin\": 1421, \"end\": 1428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Croatia\", \"score\": 0.697325317686938, \"rank\": 0.4340354106820542, \"text\": \"Croatia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Croatia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Croatia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a team\", \"from\": 1437, \"to\": 1443}, {\"ngram\": \"entitled and pampered multi\", \"from\": 1447, \"to\": 1474}, {\"ngram\": \"millionaires\", \"from\": 1475, \"to\": 1487}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It would be like rooting for that arrogant band of mostly lesbians winning the women's World Cup for America.\", \"from\": 1489, \"to\": 1598, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that arrogant band\", \"from\": 1518, \"to\": 1536}, {\"ngram\": \"mostly lesbians\", \"from\": 1540, \"to\": 1555}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's World Cup\", \"from\": 1564, \"to\": 1585}, {\"ngram\": \"America\", \"from\": 1590, \"to\": 1597}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not understand just blindly supporting someone, or some group, just because they come from your country.\", \"from\": 1599, \"to\": 1708, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 1643, \"to\": 1650}, {\"ngram\": \"some group\", \"from\": 1655, \"to\": 1665}, {\"ngram\": \"your country\", \"from\": 1695, \"to\": 1707}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But then few people have ever called me patriotic, despite my love of the Founding Fathers.\", \"from\": 1709, \"to\": 1800, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"few people\", \"from\": 1718, \"to\": 1728}, {\"ngram\": \"my love\", \"from\": 1768, \"to\": 1775}, {\"ngram\": \"the Founding Fathers\", \"from\": 1779, \"to\": 1799}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I will never get worked up, like Donald Trump did recently, over protesters burning the American flag.\", \"from\": 1801, \"to\": 1903, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1834, \"end\": 1846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.55419029428306e-19, \"text\": \"Donald Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/reso